name: Baked Fish with Frozen Vegetables
author: newcook
summary: Quick, simple, and delicious baked fish dish with vegetables. Great for any fish and could be made with things you normally have in your pantry. Serve with wild rice.
ingredients: 3 cups frozen California-blend vegetables (broccoli, carrot, cauliflower)
salt and ground black pepper to taste
directions: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Lightly grease a 2-quart baking dish with olive oil
Combine mixed vegetables, water, celery, onion, and garlic in the bottom of the prepared baking dish
Season with paprika, salt, and pepper
Lightly season cod fillets and layer on top of vegetables
Place in the preheated oven and immediately reduce the heat to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Bake until fish flakes easily with a fork, about 30 minutes
